postcontent: SHIPPING TO FFL AVAILABE for $39.  Rifle $250 OBOVintage J.STEVENS ARMS CO MODEL 66, BOLT ACTION, 22 SHORT AND 22 LONG AND 22 LONG RIFLE.The original Model 66 was in production at least by 1930 and possibly as early as 1929 and dropped from production in 1948. It replaced the Model 65 which was in Stevens price lists as early as Jan 2, 1929 and was not produced very long. The Model 66 was Stevens first attempt to market a bolt action tubular feed; magazines tube moved with the breech block.NO SERIAL NUMBER; Stevens did not serialized these rifles. It has Open sights. title: For Sale:  Ultimate PVS14 Night Vision Kit w/IR Laser
postcontent: Hello,I am selling my PVS14 Night Vision Monocular and IR laser night hunter package to offset the purchase of some thermal equipment.  This is a turn key setup..ready to go and will have you out running around in total darkness like it is daylight.  Everything is included as a package deal that is priced to sell fast!!  You get a PVS14 that is an OMNI-7 Variable Gain Intensifier.  It has no black specs.  This comes in a carry case, with carry straps and various lens covers, daylight cover/filter, HUD compass etc.  It also has the J-Arm to attach the PVS14 to a helmet mount or "skull crusher" (Norotos Helmet Mount Included)  This allows you to attach the PVS14 to your helmet using any Norotos or Wilcox shroud.  If you decide you don't want to head mount the unit, it also comes with a picatinny weapons mount.  This will allow the PVS14 to be used in conjunction with your current daylight weapon sight.  I have used it with a Trijicon ACOG, Eotech, and Aimpoint.  This mounts directly in front or behind your optic to turn it into a night vision weapon sight depending on which model of sight you currently have.  This night hunter package also includes a VITAL-2 IR Laser/Illuminator.  This is a very nice IR laser/illuminator.  This attaches to your picatinny rail via an ARMS throwlever mount.  It has a variable intensity and user selectable pulse rate.  It also includes an LED illuminator that acts as a flood light when there is no ambient light for the PVS14 to intensify.  This allows the unit to function in total darkenss.  The VITAL-2 is an IR laser/illuminator therefore it requires night vision to be seen.  I found using the PVS14 helmet mounted and aiming with the laser easier to be more functional than using the PVS14 as a dedicated weapon sight. I could move and shoot on the move using this set up.  This package cost over 4500.00 to put together...and I am pricing it to sell fast at 2900.00.  I don't think I have ever seen a deal as good as this for such good equipment but I need to offset my recent expenses.  I am available to show or sell the package just about any time.  You can call or text REDACTED.Thanks for looking

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 92
postcontent: This is a rare model of the 92.  It is a Beretta 92D with FS Frame parts installed.  The Beretta 92D double action only came with a smooth hammer and long trigger pull, but this one has 92 FS parts installed making it a standard double/single action.  The 92D guns came with the same frame as the 92FS so they accept the 92 FS trigger parts.  All that was needed was to drop in the Sear Pin, Sear Spring, Sear and swap the hammer creating a great shooting gun.  If you would rather have the double action only  it can easily be put back to that factory configuration. The 92D came with the good looking slick slide that is free from a slide mounted safety or decocker so there is no chance of inadvertently activating the safety while releasing the slide, the trade off is that it does not have a decocker so with the FS parts installed the hammer must be thumbed down before holstering.   Gun comes with a frame parts kit, and original DAO hammer, 3 holsters, 4 mags, and the original box.  Trades considered listed below.  Contact me for more pictures.  Gun has been reliable in both configurations, I have owned it for over 12 years, and cannot recall a malfuntion that was not ammo related (dud round).
